review_blob: It pours a dark reverent color that would make Jesus blush and produces an odor of majestic perfection that would make Mother Teressa give up being a nun just to have the sweet taste of Satan pass over her lips. It produces a deliciously deviant aroma of craft brew brilliance that can only be had by the few and the proud.
beer_name: Anchorage A Deal With The Devil Barleywine (Whiskey)

review_blob: This is a very good saison. This beer only improves as you allow it to warm in the glass. A great example of the farmhouse style and very rich with flavor.
Amazing IPA when fresh at the brewery. Sadly these guys dont "travel" real well.
Pretty average brew. I am personally not a big fan of chili infused beers. I find most of them to be interesting at best.
